# CodeFlowLens Cursor Rule

Use this rule when the user asks to understand code flow, review AI-written code, inspect what calls what, visualize data movement, create an interactive sequence diagram, or generate a browser-readable HTML flow walkthrough.

Follow the CodeFlowLens skill at `skill/codeflowlens/SKILL.md` when it is available in the current repository. Use `skill/codeflowlens/assets/strict-sequence-viewer-template.html` as the scaffold when starting from scratch.

If the skill file is not in the current repository, ask for the local CodeFlowLens path or use the nearest installed copy.

Core requirements:

- Output one self-contained HTML file unless the user requests otherwise.
- Define ordered actors with stable ids, labels, subtitles, kinds, and colors.
- Render sticky participants and lifelines from the same actor list.
- Position message lines from measured DOM lifeline centers, not guessed grid spans.
- Mark every flow with `data-from` and `data-to`.
- Mark every event card with stable `data-card-id` and explicit `data-actors`.
- Keep hover, focus, and click highlights first-degree only.
- Preserve colored related flow styling for clicked locks.
- Add semantic store/cache highlighting when persistence layers appear.
- Validate in a browser at `1440x900` and `1280x800` when possible.
- Report maximum actor-to-lifeline and message-endpoint deltas.
